  &lt;p id="sIrdPP"&gt;Reddit has struck deals &lt;a href="https://www.redditinc.com/blog/for-our-fan-communities-a-partnership-program-with-major-sports-leagues"&gt;with major sports leagues&lt;/a&gt;, including the NFL, NBA, and the MLB, as the company looks to boost revenue following its &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/22/24079978/reddit-ipo-public-offering-shares-power-users"&gt;move to go public&lt;/a&gt;. Through the program, Reddit will show more game highlights, behind-the-scenes videos, and ask-me-anything (AMA) sessions with players.&lt;/p&gt;
